    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="8">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershaft assembly vertical on a clean, flat surface. If previously removed,
                use a suitable driver and maul to install the countershaft bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007o8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007o8" filename="../figg13/g13007o8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 248. Locate "O" Stamped on Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark each countershaft for correct timing. Locate the "O" stamped on the countershaft and
                mark the tooth with highly visible toolmaker's dye or paint (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershafts in the fixture or on a flat surface for reassembly. Turn the
                countershafts so that the two teeth marked on each LO range gear are towards the middle (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007o9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007o9" filename="../figg13/g13007o9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 249. Align Output Shaft Between Countershafts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the output shaft between the countershafts and match the timing marks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o9">Figure 249</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the range yoke, offset side facing down, into the synchronizer sliding slot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p0">Figure 250</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p0" filename="../figg13/g13007p0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 250. Install Range Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the auxiliary housing over the countershaft assemblies and the output shaft assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p1">Figure 251</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p1" filename="../figg13/g13007p1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 251. Place Auxiliary Housing Over Countershaft Assemblies</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure the output shaft bearing spacer is on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p2">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p2" filename="../figg13/g13007p2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 252. Position New Gasket on Rear Bearing Cover Mounting Surface</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Heat the rear output bearing cone and install the bearing, tapered side down, on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p2">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the rear bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p2">Figure 252</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p3">Figure 253</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p3" filename="../figg13/g13007p3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 253. Position Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p3">Figure 253</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the six (6) retaining bolts in the non-chamfered hole, and tighten to 35 to 45
                ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p3">Figure 253</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing races (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p4">Figure 254</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p4" filename="../figg13/g13007p4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 254. Install Bearing Races</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install each auxiliary countershaft retaining strap with two 3/8 inch NC x 1 inch and one
                3/8 inch NC x 2-1/2 inch clean bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007p5">Figure 255</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007p5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007p5" filename="../figg13/g13007p5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 255. Install Auxiliary Countershaft Retaining Straps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1"></para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use an air gun. Tighten by hand until the bolts are snug.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
